      <div class=3D"comment-body"><p>"Watch bread to make sure it doesn't b=
urn" has embedded processes to it.  It reminds me of an episode of STTNG wh=
ere Data is watching water boil, to test "a watched pot never boils".  Rike=
r intervenes after Data varies how he watches and it always boils in the sa=
me amount of time.  Riker says to try "Turning it off."  Burnt toast is mor=
e complex than boiling water, but it also implies (D)esigning a system to t=
oast bread, collecting (I)nformation on the status (visual, smell), (C)ommu=
nicating that the bread is ready, if only to your self, and (E)xecuting app=
ropriately to remove the toast without injury or over/under toasting.  (DIC=
E).  Each iteration of toasting increases (T)raining, and may involve bette=
r (E)quipment for future iterations, whether using a fire or a pop-up toast=
er, or toaster oven, type of butter, and potentially other toppings like ja=
m or jelly; (A)ssessment to determine what the appropriate level of toast i=
s and if there is a better metric to measure how toasted it is, and (M)anag=
ement to determine if there is a way to multitask, or increase or decrease =
toasting to make interested parties more content. (TEAM).</p></div>
